  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a bright, open sky with a young adult man in a white top and dark pants suspended in a running leap, as if moving weightlessly through the air. The setting quickly becomes an urban rooftop world under a pale blue sky, with distant city buildings low on the horizon. A young man in a teal athletic shirt is seen from below with one arm extended, his dark hair lifted by motion. Another athletic man in a gray shirt and black shorts runs along the top of a rooftop structure, facing forward, then the action shifts to a soccer player in a teal jersey, black shorts, teal socks, and cleats. He floats sideways in midair, legs scissored, aiming a kick at a black-and-white soccer ball drifting above him. As he twists and tucks his body, large white outlined letters spelling “AIR” appear against the sky beside him.\n\nMore men are shown in slow, graceful airborne movement. A Black man with short curly hair, wearing a loose white shirt, dark shorts, and black shoes, arches backward in a flip, his arms open and his shirt billowing. A long-haired man is shown in profile, his brown hair blowing across his face. Another young man in a black tank top and dark pants faces forward with both arms extended like wings, his short dark hair standing up from the motion. The images emphasize hair moving freely in the air. A close view fills the screen with thick brown hair streaming sideways, individual strands and lighter highlights visible.\n\nA lineup of Just For Men product boxes appears on a clean pale blue background. The boxes stand in a row, each showing the upper face and hair of a different man on the front. The nearest box is largest, with the “Just For Men” logo and “Autostop” visible, along with a red side panel and a shade label reading “Medium Brown.” Smaller boxes behind it show other hair colors and faces, arranged diagonally into the background.\n\nThe rooftop action resumes over a downtown skyline. A pair of legs in black shoes cros